<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1468,1671]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davies" authorityYear="2005" box="[372,581,1468,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acanthophorus">
<emphasis box="[372,581,1468,1495]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">S. acanthophorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here described for the first time. It can be separated from other species of this group by the combination of the following characters: clypeus distinctly convex (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C–D), foretibia dominantly blackish-brown, stigma brown, apical margins of metasomal terga broadly brownish translucent, terga between punctures smooth and shiny (
<figureCitation box="[955,1044,1574,1600]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). The male is characterized by an unmodified antenna, hind tibia apically broadened inside forming a spine (
<figureCitation box="[1082,1171,1609,1635]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
), coarsely but more sparsely punctate scutum and metasomal terga (
<figureCitation box="[749,839,1644,1670]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) and the form of S7 (
<figureCitation box="[1092,1186,1644,1670]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
