<paragraph blockId="4.[189,506,314,375]" box="[189,506,348,375]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
BODY LENGTH. 6.0– 
<quantity box="[409,501,348,375]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1398,414,476]" lastBlockId="5.[189,1398,267,364]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
HEAD. Head wider than long. Integument black except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[729,819,449,475]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
). Clypeus strongly convex with coarse punctation, apically sparse (i = 2–3 d), basally dense (i = 0.5–1 d); surface between punctures apically smooth and shiny, basally superficially shagreened and slightly matt (
<figureCitation box="[914,980,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C–D). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally blackish-brown, ventrally yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" startId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" targetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" targetPageId="4">
