. Head. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,210,1937,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">D</emphasis>
. Head (SEM). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[397,417,1937,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">E</emphasis>
. Thorax (dorsal view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[703,721,1937,1963]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">F</emphasis>
. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,403,500]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures superficially shagreened but shiny; disc densely (i = 0.5–1.0 d) and coarsely punctate (
<figureCitation box="[801,868,438,464]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
E–F). Metanotum slightly shorter than basal area of propodeum, apically with narrow carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[933,1024,473,500]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Propodeum basally finely but
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" startId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" targetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[187,1399,1930,2027]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[187,266,1930,1956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Davies, 2005" authorityName="Davies" authorityYear="2005" box="[274,726,1930,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Scrapter" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acanthophorus">
<emphasis box="[274,559,1930,1957]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Scrapter acanthophorus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Davies G. B. P. &amp; Eardley C. D. &amp; Brothers D. J." box="[567,726,1930,1957]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="141 - 179" refId="ref26814" refString="Davies G. B. P., Eardley C. D. &amp; Brothers D. J. 2005. Eight new species of Scrapter (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Colletidae), with descriptions of S. albifumus and S. amplispinatus females and a major range extension of the genus. African Invertebrates 46: 141 - 179." type="journal article" year="2005">Davies, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, ♂. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[775,796,1930,1956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A</emphasis>
. Lateral view. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[974,994,1930,1956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">B</emphasis>
. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1370,1391,1930,1956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">C</emphasis>
. Metasoma (dorsal view). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[487,508,1965,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">D</emphasis>
. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[804,824,1965,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">E</emphasis>
. Hind tibia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[971,989,1965,1991]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">F</emphasis>
. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,267,329]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
broadly carinate (
<figureCitation box="[391,478,267,293]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[649,742,302,329]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,986,368,394]" box="[189,986,368,394]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">WINGS. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,433,495]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">LEGS. Integument black to dark reddish-brown; fore and mid tibia basally with small yellowish spot. Vestiture greyish-white, scopa greyish-white.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,534,771]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga broadly translucent yellowish to reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[198,288,569,595]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Discs of T1 and T2 without hair, laterally sparsely covered with long erect greyish-white hair; following terga with increasingly more and longer hair; T3–T4 basally with a very narrow and sparse band of very fine, short, erect hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[1105,1194,640,666]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae greyish-brown. T1 densely (i = 1 d) but finely punctate, between punctures polished and shiny; T2–T4 shiny, with dense, fine, superficial punctation; T2–T4 with polished broad apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[404,495,745,771]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1902,1928]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,527,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[189,1399,527,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♀. A. Lateral view. B. Metasoma (dorsal view). C. Head. D. Head (SEM). E. Thorax (dorsal view). F. Thorax (dorsal view, SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860598/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,506,811,873]" box="[234,298,811,837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[234,298,811,837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,506,811,873]" box="[189,506,846,873]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">BODY LENGTH. 5.2–6.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,911,1008]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
HEAD. Head slightly wider than long. Integument black, except mandible partly dark reddish-brown. Face densely covered with long, greyish-white, erect hair. Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally dark brown, ventrally yellowish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[873,968,982,1008]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1047,1144]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">MESOSOMA. Integument black. Mesoscutal disc between punctures superficially shagreened but shiny; disc densely (i = 0.5–1.0 d) and coarsely punctate. Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum covered with long, greyish, erect hair.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,986,1183,1210]" box="[189,986,1183,1210]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">WINGS. Slightly yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1399,1248,1345]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
LEGS. Integument black, fore tarsi and inner side of fore tibia yellow, base of mid tibia with small yellow spot (
<figureCitation box="[255,351,1284,1310]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Hind tibia inside apically broadened, with a spine; hind basitarsus medially broadened (
<figureCitation box="[198,289,1319,1345]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
). Vestiture greyish-white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1398,1384,1622]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga broadly translucent yellowish to reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[198,292,1419,1446]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). Discs of T1–T3 without hair, laterally sparsely covered with short, erect greyish-white hair; following terga with increasingly more and longer hair; T2–T4 basally with a very narrow and sparse band of very fine, short, erect hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[1191,1288,1490,1516]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). T1 and following terga densely (i ˂ 0.5–1 d) but finely punctate, between punctures polished or superficially sculptured, shiny to slightly matt; terga with broad, polished to superficially sculptured but shiny apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[404,497,1595,1622]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
). S3 and particularly S4–S5 with long apical hair fringes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[189,1286,1661,1687]" box="[189,1286,1661,1687]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
TERMINALIA. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[460,552,1661,1687]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
), S7 (
<figureCitation box="[621,713,1661,1687]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) and terminal plate of S8 (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1114,1661,1687]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="5.[187,230,1930,1956]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,559,1889]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[189,1399,559,1889]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 2. Scrapter acanthophorus Davies, 2005, ♂. A. Lateral view. B. Genitalia (dorsal view, SEM). C. Metasoma (dorsal view). D. S7 (dorsal view, SEM). E. Hind tibia. F. S8, apical end (SEM). Scale bars: photos: 1 mm, SEM: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3860600" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3860600/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
) as illustrated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
